ahamanowicz@astrouw.edu.pl
pietruk@astrouw.edu.pl
udalski@astrouw.edu.pl


This directory contains details on detected variables in the globular
cluster M54 (NGC 6715) residing in the core of the Sgr dSph galaxy.

The directory structure is as follows:

README            - this file

M54variables.dat  - list of variable stars in M54

phot/I/           - I-band photometry of individual variables
phot/V/           - V-band photometry of individual variables
phot.tar.gz       - gzipped phot/ directory

fcharts/          - finding charts of individual variables

pap.pdf           - PDF version of the publication


Format of the file M54variables.dat:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Bytes  Format Units   Description
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
   1-  4  A4    ---     Variable's ID
   7- 10  A4    ---     HST variable candidate's ID (Montiel & Mighell 2010)
  13- 14  I2    h       Right ascension, equinox J2000.0 (hours)
  16- 17  I2    m       Right ascension, equinox J2000.0 (minutes)
  18- 22  F5.2  s       Right ascension, equinox J2000.0 (seconds)
      25  A1    ---     Declination, equinox J2000.0 (sign)
  26- 27  I2    deg     Declination, equinox J2000.0 (degrees)
  29- 30  I2    arcmin  Declination, equinox J2000.0 (arc minutes)
  32- 35  F4.1  arcsec  Declination, equinox J2000.0 (arc seconds)
  39- 44  F6.3  arcmin  Distance from the center of the cluster
  47- 53  F7.3  r_c     Distance from the center in units of M54 core radius
  56- 61  F6.3  r_h     Distance from the center in units of M54 half-light radius 
  64- 68  F5.3  r_t     Distance from the center in units of M54 tidal radius
  71- 90  A20   ---     OGLE-BLG-RRLYR-ID (Soszynski et al. 2014)
  93-107  A15   ---     OGLE-IV ID
 110-121  F12.8 d       Period
 124-134  F10.8 d       Period uncertainty
 136-140  I5    ---     OGLE-IV ID in the V band
 147-153  A7    ---     Variability type
 155-160  F6.3  mag     Mean V-band brightness
 163-168  F6.3  mag     Maximum V-band brightness
 171-176  F6.3  mag     Minimum V-band brightness
 179-184  F6.3  mag     Mean I-band brightness
 187-192  F6.3  mag     Maximum I-band brightness
 195-200  F6.3  mag     Minimum I-band brightness
 203-207  F5.3  mag     I-band amplitude
 210-260  A     ---     Remarks
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Finding charts are gzipped Postscript images. The finding charts are
30"x30" subframes of the I-band reference frames centered on the star.
White cross marks the star. North is up and East to the left. Some stars
in the center of the cluster are hardly visible due to crowding.


Any presentation of the scientific analysis or usage of the data from the
OGLE collection of variable stars should include appropriate references
to OGLE papers.
